quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,10,"He is the One Who sends down rain from the sky, from which you drink and by which plants grow for your cattle to graze"
  16,11,"With it He produces for you ˹various˺ crops, olives, palm trees, grapevines, and every type of fruit. Surely in this is a sign for those who reflect"
  16,12,"And He has subjected for your benefit the day and the night, the sun and the moon. And the stars have been subjected by His command. Surely in this are signs for those who understand"
  16,13,And ˹He subjected˺ for you whatever He has created on earth of varying colours. Surely in this is a sign for those who are mindful
  16,14,"And He is the One Who has subjected the sea, so from it you may eat tender seafood and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships ploughing their way through it, so you may seek His bounty and give thanks ˹to Him˺"
  16,15,"He has placed into the earth firm mountains, so it does not shake with you, as well as rivers, and pathways so you may find your way"
  16,16,Also by landmarks and stars do people find their way
  16,17,Can the One Who creates be equal to those who do not? Will you not then be mindful
  16,18,"If you tried to count God’s blessings, you would never be able to number them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,19,And God knows what you conceal and what you reveal
  16,20,But those ˹idols˺ they invoke besides God cannot create anything—they themselves are created
  16,21,"They are dead, not alive—not even knowing when their followers will be resurrected"